- [ ] 1 Diced Onion
- [ ] 2 Tbsp tomato purée 
- [ ] 400g Diced Chicken Breast
- [ ] 140g Diced Chorizo
- [ ] 700ml Chicken Stock
- [ ] 260g Rice
- [ ] 3 Crushed Garlic Cloves 
- [ ] 120g Grated Mature Cheddar
- [ ] 1 Tsp Smoked Paprika
- [ ] 1 Tsp Garlic Granules
- [ ] 1 Tsp Onion Granules

1. Firstly fry off your onion and chorizo. After a few mins add your garlic and fry for 30 secs.

2. The add your chicken, Garlic Granules and Paprika once your chicken has some colour all over then add in your Tomato Purée.

3. Add in your uncooked rice, stir for another minute or so and then add your stock, bring this to a boil. Once boiling reduce the heat to low and cover the pan then leave to cook for 15/20 mins. Stir occasionally!

1. Once the rice is done, scatter over the cheese and sprinkle the parsley.
